HEADWORD: Polacca
<hw>Po*lac"ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>polacca</ets>, <ets>polaccra</ets>, <ets>polacra</ets>; cf. F.
<ets>polaque</ets>, <ets>polacre</ets>, Sp. <ets>polacre</ets>,]</ety>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>polacre</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A vessel with two or three masts, used in the
Mediterranean. The masts are usually of one piece, and without tops,
caps, or crosstrees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>See <er>Polonaise</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polack</ent>⟦br⟧
